General.Name: Kewpie Corporation
General.Description: Kewpie Corporation, through its subsidiaries, manufactures and sales food products in Japan and internationally. It offers mayonnaise dressings, pasta sauces, baby food, nursing care food, and packaged salads; liquid eggs, frozen eggs, vinegar, seasonings, cooking sauces, omelets, egg salads, etc.; baby food products; and jams and spreads, as well as hyaluronic acid, egg yolk lecithin, etc. The company also provides bottled and canned food and other various food articles, food additives, and feeds and fertilizers; and equipment for food articles and medical drugs, and other various machines and equipment. Further, it engages in the plumbing work, machinery and equipment installation work, construction work, and electrical work businesses; building designing, construction, supervisory, and consulting business; lease of real estate; and operation and management of food processing equipment business. The company was founded in 1919 and is headquartered in Shibuya, Japan.
